definitions.definition: Language, particularly written language, not intended as poetry.
examples: Though known mostly for her prose , she also produced a small body of excellent poems.

definitions.definition: Language which evinces little imagination or animation; dull and commonplace discourse.
A hymn with no regular meter , sometimes introduced into the Mass.
